\f0\fs28 \cf2 ### \cf4 Option One: CrystalsCollector Game (Recommended)
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 ![\cf4 Crystal Collector\cf2 ](\cf6 Images/1-CrystalCollector.jpg\cf2 )
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 1.\cf4  \cf2 [\cf4 Watch the demo\cf2 ](\cf6 homework_demos/crystalsCollector_demo.mp4\cf2 )\cf4 .
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 2.\cf4  The player will have to guess the answer, just like in Hangman. This time, though, the player will guess with numbers instead of letters. 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 3.\cf4  Here's how the app works:
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  There will be four crystals displayed as buttons on the page.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player will be shown a random number at the start of the game.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  When the player clicks on a crystal, it will add a specific amount of points to the player's total score. 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4      \cf2 *\cf4  Your game will hide this amount until the player clicks a crystal.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 \cf4      \cf2 *\cf4  When they do click one, update the player's score counter.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player wins if their total score matches the random number from the beginning of the game.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player loses if their score goes above the random number.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The game restarts whenever the player wins or loses.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4      \cf2 *\cf4  When the game begins again, the player should see a new random number. Also, all the crystals will have four new hidden values. Of course, the user's score (and score counter) will reset to zero.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The app should show the number of games the player wins and loses. To that end, do not refresh the page as a means to restart the game.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs28 \cf2 ##### \cf4 Option 1 Game design notes
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  The random number shown at the start of the game should be between 19 - 120.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  Each crystal should have a random hidden value between 1 - 12.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
