\f0\fs28 \cf2 ### \cf4 Option Two: Star Wars RPG Game (Challenge)
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 ![\cf4 Star Wars\cf2 ](\cf6 Images/2-StarWars.jpg\cf2 )
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 1.\cf4  \cf2 [\cf4 Watch the demo\cf2 ](\cf6 homework_demos/starwars_demo.mp4\cf2 )\cf4 .
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 2.\cf4  Here's how the app works:
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  When the game starts, the player will choose a character by clicking on the fighter's picture. The player will fight as that character for the rest of the game.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player must then defeat all of the remaining fighters. Enemies should be moved to a different area of the screen.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player chooses an opponent by clicking on an enemy's picture.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  Once the player selects an opponent, that enemy is moved to a \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 defender area
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 .
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  The player will now be able to click the \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 attack
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  button.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 \cf4      \cf2 *\cf4  Whenever the player clicks \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 attack
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 , their character damages the defender. The opponent will lose \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 HP
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  (health points). These points are displayed at the bottom of the defender's picture. 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 \cf4      \cf2 *\cf4  The opponent character will instantly counter the attack. When that happens, the player's character will lose some of their \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 HP
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 . These points are shown at the bottom of the player character's picture.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 3.\cf4  The player will keep hitting the attack button in an effort to defeat their opponent.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4    \cf2 *\cf4  When the defender's \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 HP
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  is reduced to zero or below, remove the enemy from the \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 defender area
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 . The player character can now choose a new opponent.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 4.\cf4  The player wins the game by defeating all enemy characters. The player loses the game the game if their character's \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 HP
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  falls to zero or below.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs28 \cf2 ##### \cf4 Option 2 Game design notes
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  Each character in the game has 3 attributes: \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Health Points
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 , \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  and \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Counter Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 .
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  Each time the player attacks, their character's Attack Power increases by its base Attack Power. 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 \cf4   \cf2 *\cf4  For example, if the base Attack Power is 6, each attack will increase the Attack Power by 6 (12, 18, 24, 30 and so on).
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  The enemy character only has \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Counter Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 . 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4   \cf2 *\cf4  Unlike the player's \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Attack Points
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 , \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Counter Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  never changes.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  The \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Health Points
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 , \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  and \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Counter Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  of each character must differ.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  No characters in the game can heal or recover Health Points. 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf4   \cf2 *\cf4  A winning player must pick their characters wisely by first fighting an enemy with low \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Counter Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 . This will allow them to grind \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Attack Power
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4  and to take on enemies before they lose all of their \cf2 `
\f2\fs24 \cf5 Health Points
\f0\fs26 \cf2 `\cf4 . Healing options would mess with this dynamic.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\

\f0\fs26 \cf2 *\cf4  Your players should be able to win and lose the game no matter what character they choose. The challenge should come from picking the right enemies, not choosing the strongest player.
\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
